.TH "read_persistent_clock64" 9 "read_persistent_clock64" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
read_persistent_clock64 \- Return time from the persistent clock.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" read_persistent_clock64
.BI "(struct timespec64 *ts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ts" 12
Pointer to the storage for the readout value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Weak dummy function for arches that do not yet support it.
Reads the time from the battery backed persistent clock.
Returns a timespec with tv_sec=0 and tv_nsec=0 if unsupported.

